<section xml:id="sec-notation" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Scientific Notation Reminder</title>

  <introduction>
<p>
    When Excel calculates very small probabilities, it often shows the result in <em>scientific notation</em>.
</p>

  </introduction>

  <p>
Suppose you use Excel to calculate a probability and it gives the output:
<code>
4.7E-08
</code>.
  </p>
  <p>
This means:
<me>
4.7\times 10^{-8}=0.000000047
</me>
  </p>
  <p>
So the probability is <m>0.000000047</m>, which is very small!
  </p>

        <exercise>

            <introduction>
                <p>
                    Convert each probability from Excel's scientific notation into standard decimal form:
                </p>
            </introduction>

                <task>
                    <statement>
                    <p>
                        Excel outputs <code> 2.3E-05 </code>.  Write this probability as a decimal.
                    </p>
                    </statement>
                    <answer>
                        <m> 0.000023</m>
                    </answer>
                </task>

                <task>
                    <statement>
                    <p>
                        Excel outputs <code> 7.1E-04 </code>.  Write this probability as a decimal.
                    </p>
                    </statement>
                    <answer>
                        <m> 0.00071</m>
                    </answer>
                </task>

                <task>
                    <statement>
                    <p>
                        Excel outputs <code> 9.6E-07 </code>.  Write this probability as a decimal.
                    </p>
                    </statement>
                    <answer>
                        <m> 0.00000096</m>
                    </answer>
                </task>

                <task>
                    <statement>
                    <p>
                        Excel outputs <code> 1.2E-02 </code>.  Write this probability as a decimal.
                    </p>
                    </statement>
                    <answer>
                        <m> 0.012</m>
                    </answer>
                </task>


        </exercise>


</section>


